list.t:
clarified that BFCP and CCMP-based media control are neither in conflict nor
				one the wrapper of the other; they act at different levels, and when both are involved,
				it is required that both grant a resource before it can be used by an interested participant;

clarified that a successful creation of a new conference object may or may not
				contain the whole confInfo object in the response; in case it doesn't, a retrieve
				of the updated object can be achieved by issuing a confRequest/retrieve;
